        <p><strong>Atlassian</strong> is an Australian enterprise software company that develops products geared towards software developers and project managers. It is best known for its issue tracking application, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('JIRA', 'ITS'); ?>, and its team collaboration product, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Confluence', 'ITS'); ?>. Atlassian serves over 35,000 customers globally, including 85 of the Fortune 100.</p>
        <p>Atlassian is headquartered in Sydney, Australia. It also has offices in Amsterdam, San Francisco, Austin and Tokyo. As of September 2014, the company has over 1,148 employees, offices in 12 cities, over 40,000 customers and many millions of users. On 14 February 2014, Atlassian president Jay Simons announced the opening of an Austin office that will eventually employ 600 people.</p>
